  "time_ut": 1661741981,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dda \u0db8\u0da7\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db8 \u0d95\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Oh God, I don't want the prime ministership",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena, the leader of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party, said that although the Sri Lanka Freedom Party proposed to the government from the beginning that it would be possible to solve the problems in the country through the formation of an all-party government, the current president is ignoring the request and is trying to form a traditional government instead of an all-party government. .",
        "The former president said that his party proposed that an all-party government should be formed by limiting the cabinet minister positions to twenty and further said that the 30 government cabinet minister positions and the 40 state minister positions that will be created in the future will be given.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena said this while addressing the first Constituency Board meeting organized at a function hall in Thalavathugoda last (28) after the new constituency organizer of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party, Mr. Saman Pushpakumara Lankeswara, assumed his position in the Maharagama Constituency.",
        "I remember Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that an all-party government should be formed in the truest sense of the word. Having said that, my friend Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva joined the government and took a ministership the next day. After that they said in the media that they joined the government with the approval of the party Central Committee and on the advice of the President Maithripala Sirisena. It's a flat out lie. They were never given my or the party's approval.",
        "In that way, an all-party government has not been established. A traditional government. We have heard that in the future, 30 cabinet ministers, 40 state ministers and 40 ministers are going to be formed. This is not an all-party government. It is a traditional government. We have no agreement for that. We proposed to form a new government with twenty ministers. But that didn't happen. In the meantime, others are suggesting me to take over the prime ministership of the new government. Oh God, I don't want to be the prime minister.",
        "Even though a new president has been appointed, the leaders of the Pohottu party are still ruling this country. That is the true story. Because the largest number of MPs in the Parliament are in Pohotta, so if any bill is passed, it should be done with their help. So I am not going to take any position in such a government. The party does not approve it. If someone leaves the party and joins the government, it is not to build the country but to get positions. That is our policy. These rulers have no plan to solve the existing problems. Only the Sri Lanka Freedom Party has the solutions for that.\""
      ],
